-- Carrefour May Eliminate Up to 5,000 French Jobs, Reuters Says
-- B y   A n d r e w   R o b e r t s
-- 2012-04-27T13:28:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-27/carrefour-may-eliminate-up-to-5-000-french-jobs-reuters-says.html
Carrefour SA (CA)  Chief Executive
Officer-designate Georges Plassat may cut 3,000 to 5,000 jobs at
the retailer in France, Reuters reported, citing a
representative of the  Force Ouvriere  union.  Plassat will meet unions on May 10, Reuters said, citing
Dejan Terglav, the union official. Plassat joined the world’s
second-largest retailer as chief operating officer this month
and will become CEO in June.  Carrefour, based in Boulogne-Billancourt, France, declined
to comment. Calls to Terglav’s mobile phone went unanswered.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Andrew Roberts  in Paris at 
 aroberts36@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
